    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSometimes when using visual mode and then using H or L, the selection is drawn incorrectly. But this only happens when `scrolloff` is a positive number.\n\nExample:\n\n<img width=\"1045\" height=\"753\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aab668a7-dfdd-477f-ad33-f87770020532\" />\n\nNote the cursor is at the bottom, and the visual selection started near the top, but the visual selection is only drawn on the top line (it's also missing in the spot that the cursor was before I pressed `L`). If I now press `l` to move the cursor, or CTRL+L to redraw the screen, the visual selection gets drawn correctly:\n\n<img width=\"1045\" height=\"753\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eac1c31c-cd82-492c-85a5-c4bcffd66192\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:e $VIMRUNTIME/example_init.lua\n:set scrolloff=2\n/Case\nz<CR>\nV\nL\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe visual selection is drawn correctly, as in the second image I posted above.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1775\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora Linux 42\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome terminal 48.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ndnf install neovim",
